article.headline: Lasme gets third triple-double of season in UMass win
article.linkText: Lasme gets third triple-double of season in UMass win
article.story:
AMHERST, Mass. -- Stephane Lasme had 18 points, 12 rebounds and 11 blocked shots to lead Massachusetts to a 77-55 victory over Rhode Island on Thursday night. Gary Forbes scored a game-high 22 points for UMass (17-6, 7-2), which built a 23-5 lead to start the game. Lasme delivered his third triple-double of the season as Massachusetts moved into first place in the Atlantic 10. Lasme, who also had triple-doubles against St. Francis and George Washington, is the eighth player in NCAA history with three or more triple-doubles in a season. Drexel's Michael Anderson set the NCAA record of four in 1986, a mark Cal's Jason Kidd tied in 1994. The Rams (14-10, 7-3) didn't score from the field until Jimmy Baron drove for a layup with 8:52 to play in the first half. Baron scored 17 points and Joe Mbang added 10 for Rhode Island. UMass led 41-27 at halftime and had no trouble holding off Rhode Island, which shot 26.6 percent from the field for the game. Lasme had 13 points before intermission for UMass, which had lost at Rhode Island by three points two weeks ago.

Information from The Associated Press was used in this report.
